<p><img alt="The Learning Model at the Academic Discovery Center" height="270" src="Images/advising/aa-and-cp/lmodel.jpg" title="The Learning Model at the Academic Discovery Center" width="710" /></p>
<p>Understanding and applying the Learning Model is fundamental to your success at Brigham Young University-Idaho.  We invite you to go to this site and learn what the Learning Model is and how it can bless your life: <a href="http://www.byui.edu/learningmodel/src/default.htm" title="Learning Model" target="_blank">BYU-Idaho Learning Model</a>.</p>
<p>As you put the learning model into action, you will find answers to your questions, instructions to guide your actions and a much more satisfying experience as you navigate your academic life at BYU-Idaho.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>The Academic Discovery Center invites you to apply the steps from the Learning Model by doing the following:</strong></p>
<h3>1. Prepare</h3>
<p>Prepare before you call or visit your major's Academic Discovery Center by reviewing the information on this web site. You will find that many of your questions will be answered and you will be better prepared for an effective, efficient session when you visit our offices.</p>
<h3>2. Learn and Teach</h3>
<p>Bring the information that you gathered in your preparation and visit your major's Academic Discovery Center to gain additional details and insights for your academic plan.</p>
<h3>3. Ponder and Prove</h3>
<p>Follow the advising counsel you are given in a timely manner. Acting promptly according to the information discussed is an important part of your accountability and gives you an opportunity to "prove" the instructions you've received.</p>
